doc.after: There are about 3,000 runestones among the about 6,000 runic inscriptions in Scandinavia.[3] There are also runestones in other parts of the world as the tradition of raising runestones followed the Norsemen wherever they went, from the Isle of Man (Manx Runestones) in the west to the Black Sea in the east (Berezan' Runestone), and from JÃ¤mtland in the north to Schleswig in the south.[2]
